title: Most popular online dating services in selected countries as of February 2014
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 9 different Countrys on X-axis for 6 groups Facebook, Twitter, MySpace, Shaadi, Match, and Badoo. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Percentage of respondents.
Out of all 6 groups, Facebook had the highest Percentage of respondents for Country Vietnam and MySpace had the lowest Percentage of respondents for Country India.
The maximum Percentage of respondents for MySpace that was found in Country Kenya was 0 times larger than the minimum Percentage of respondents observed in Country India.
Averaging all 6 groups Facebook, Twitter, MySpace, Shaadi, Match, and Badoo, the Country Indonesia is the maximum Percentage of respondents and Brazil is the minimum Percentage of respondents.

For Country Vietnam, Facebook had the highest Percentage of respondents 85.0 among the 6 groups and in India, MySpace had the lowest Percentage of respondents 0.0.

Among all 6 groups, Facebook had the gap of 36.0 between the maximum and minimum Percentage of respondents observed in Country Vietnam and Brazil respectively.

In case of Country Vietnam, Facebook had the highest Percentage of respondents 85.0 among the 6 groups and in India, MySpace had the lowest Percentage of respondents 0.0. The second highest Percentage of respondents 14.0 was observed for Facebook in Country Vietnam.

On average, the Country Indonesia had the highest Percentage of respondents for all 6 groups Facebook, Twitter, MySpace, Shaadi, Match, and Badoo. Whereas Brazil had the lowest average Percentage of respondents.
